</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFSQbh hsMkcS pf-168_"><b>Sensitive skin: </b>Because red light treatments are gentle and non-invasive, they’re appropriate for sensitive skin. In fact, they can even help fade redness and even out the skin tone through a soothing and reparative effect.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFSQbh hsMkcS pf-170_"><b>Acne-prone skin:</b> You can undergo red light treatments even if you have acne-prone skin, and their soothing effect can help visibly fade blemishes for clearer skin. </li><div class="sc-cTAqQK cFxQA-d pf-172_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jNHqnW irErrH pf-173_"></div></div></div></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-b436" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dYtuZ WVull pf-174_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eZhRLC gtfCKx"><div class="sc-cTAqQK cFxQA-d pf-175_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jNHqnW irErrH pf-176_"><div class="sc-cTAqQK cFxQA-d pf-177_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-to-section="pf-7040" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c pf-hide" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jNHqnW irErrH pf-178_ pf-hide"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jNHqnW irErrH pf-179_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-nVkyK bhIDty pf-180_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-182_">Picking a Red Light Therapy Device</span></h2><p class="sc-gDGHff eHTxVX pf-183_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-185_">If you’d like to introduce red light therapy into your daily care routine, all you need to do is pick up a device! Nowadays, there are many options available, including masks, glasses, and wands. <br><br>&nbsp;At Evertone, we developed a 4-in-1 <a href="/products/evertone-red-light-therapy-wand" target="_self"><u>red light therapy Infrawave wand </u></a>that rejuvenates the skin, with the addition of vibrational massage and microcurrent stimulation. This combination of effects gives the skin a serious boost. With a regular 5-minute session you can fade fine lines, reduce puffiness, firm your skin, and clear away blemishes! The best part? It’s an incredibly affordable option that costs about half the price of a red light facial at a salon! 
<a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1743919115010110" target="_self"></a></span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-931c" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dYtuZ WVull pf-186_ pf-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eZhRLC gtfCKx"><div class="sc-cTAqQK cFxQA-d pf-187_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-66dd" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dYtuZ WVull pf-188_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eZhRLC gtfCKx"><div class="sc-cTAqQK cFxQA-d pf-189_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-to-section="pf-6957" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c pf-hide" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jNHqnW irErrH pf-190_ pf-hide"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jNHqnW irErrH pf-191_"><div class="sc-cTAqQK cFxQA-d pf-192_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jNHqnW irErrH pf-193_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-nVkyK bhIDty pf-194_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-196_">Tips for Using Red Light Therapy at Home</span></h3><p class="sc-lcepkR datYlM pf-197_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span contenteditable="true" placeholder="Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur." data-text-editing="true" spellcheck="false" class="sc-hiwPVj iaRKMD">Here’s how to use red light therapy at home, and ensure you achieve the best results!
<br>
</span></p></div></div></div><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-jwQYvw gWEXlz pf-199_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFSQbh hsMkcS pf-200_">Always start with clean skin. Use a gentle, oil-free cleanser that’ll remove sebum and other debris from your skin, and make sure to rinse it away well. 
 
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFSQbh hsMkcS pf-202_">Consider also exfoliating your skin to eliminate dead skin cells and help the light reach even deeper. 
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFSQbh hsMkcS pf-204_">Next, apply a water-based, hydrating serum (hyaluronic acid serums are excellent). 
 </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFSQbh hsMkcS pf-206_">Finally, use your LED light device. With a tool like the Evertone Infrawave wand, you can simply turn the device on, and glide it over your skin. Always massage upwards and outwards to give your skin more of a lift.  
 </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFSQbh hsMkcS pf-208_">Don’t forget to use your red light device over other body parts where you have specific concerns, like your chest or neck. 
  
 </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFSQbh hsMkcS pf-210_">Once you’re done, finish off your skincare routine with the rest of your products, and don’t forget to apply moisturizer.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFSQbh hsMkcS pf-212_">If you’ve used your device in the daytime, make sure to also use sunscreen.&nbsp;</li><div class="sc-cTAqQK cFxQA-d pf-214_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jNHqnW irErrH pf-215_"></div></div></div></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-5f91" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dYtuZ WVull pf-216_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eZhRLC gtfCKx"><div class="sc-cTAqQK cFxQA-d pf-217_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-to-section="pf-af42" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c pf-hide" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jNHqnW irErrH pf-218_ pf-hide"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jNHqnW irErrH pf-219_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-nVkyK bhIDty pf-220_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-222_">Addressing Common Concerns </span></h2><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-nVkyK bhIDty pf-223_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-225_">How often should you use red light therapy on your face?</span></h3><p class="sc-lcepkR datYlM pf-226_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><br>For the best results, use your home red LED light device at least three to four times a week. You don’t need to worry about overdoing red light therapy, so if you have more time, you can even use it on a daily basis either in the morning or at night. </p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-nVkyK bhIDty pf-228_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-230_">Are there any contraindications or precautions?</span></h3><p class="sc-lcepkR datYlM pf-231_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><br>Home red light therapy devices are a very safe option for almost everyone. That said, if you have epilepsy, eye conditions that impact your sight, or you take medications that cause photosensitivity, you may want to speak to your doctor before undergoing red light therapy. </p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-nVkyK bhIDty pf-233_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-235_">What are the potential side effects of red light therapy?</span></h3><p class="sc-lcepkR datYlM pf-236_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">There are no serious side effects associated with the gentle red light therapy devices used at home. Stronger machines may lead to some skin irritation or cause eye strain, especially when it comes to masks, but wands are a particularly safe choice. </p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-nVkyK bhIDty pf-238_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eoHXOn hKPgxQ pf-240_">Can red light therapy be used during pregnancy or while breastfeeding?</span></h3><p class="sc-lcepkR datYlM pf-241_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Pregnancy is generally not considered a contraindication for red light therapy. In fact, dim red light has been <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27821114/" target="_self"><u>studied as a potential treatment</u></a> for depressive symptoms during pregnancy. Even so, we highly recommend that you speak to your doctor before undergoing red light treatments if you’re pregnant or breastfeeding.&nbsp;</p><div class="sc-cTAqQK cFxQA-d pf-243_ pf-r pf-r-eh pf-hide" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-5f62" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-d